description: In Nation of Language’s interview with Host Zach McCormick, Ian Richard Devaney touched on his personal journey with grief, as well as the private and public moments that come with it.
title: @NationofLanguage touching on the private and public moments that come with grief. #shorts

author: The Current
description:
To celebrate The Current’s 20th Anniversary, The Current’s Live Sessions Vault unlocks never-before-seen live performance videos of bands and artists who have played in our iconic studio. 

Watch to see the full session and interview of John Grant featuring previously unreleased footage, from when he visited The Current studio back in 2015.

Songs Performed 
00:00:00 Global Warming
00:04:06 Down Here
00:07:52 Grey Tickles, Black Pressure

Musicians
John Grant — vocals, piano
Chris Pemberton — vocals, keyboard
Petur Hallgrimsson — guitar

Credits
Engineer – Corey Schreppel, Dan Mariska
Producer – Lindsay Kimball
Visuals  – Nate Ryan
Digital Producer – Natalia Toledo
Graphics – Natalia Toledo

The Current’s Live Sessions Vault is supported by the Minnesota Orchestra, GS Motors, and Delta Dental of Minnesota Foundation.
